A helpless horse was pulled from a raging river after a gruelling two hour fight for survival.

The 500lb wild filly was spotted struggling to stay upright in strong currents after getting trapped by boulders in Trout Creek in Summerland, British Columbia.

Theresa Nolet, 59, from Ontario, Canada, captured the amazing rescue on camera as volunteers, fire fighters and police officers attempted to pull the horse out of the cold water.

