Theresa said: ‘It was a heart-stopper, that's for sure - seeing her slip out of the rope and slide down the river.

‘Just as we would get the rope around her, she would slip right out again.’

It took rescuers four attempts before successfully getting a rope around the horse's neck, allowing them to steadily bring her closer to shore.

